OL,3,COfsted to keep single-phrase ratings
OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,FMr Whiteman added: "The government's
OL,7,Fdefence of discredited, simplistic,
OL,8,Fand reductive single-word or phrase
OL,9,Fjudgements simply perpetuates an
OL,10,Finhumane and unreliable inspection
OL,11,Fsystem that is driving a mental health
OL,12,Fand wellbeing crisis across England's
OL,13,Fschools."
OL,15,FPepe Di'Iasio, general secretary of
OL,16,Fthe Association of School and College
OL,17,FLeaders (ASCL), said: "The
OL,18,FGovernment's response to the call for
OL,19,Fan alternative to single-phrase
OL,20,Fjudgments is deeply disappointing.
OL,26,@nD@TOUuD@IO]yD@WOU
