OL,3,COfsted to keep single-phrase ratings
OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,F"The problem is not presentational; it
OL,7,Fis that the system is fundamentally
OL,8,Fflawed and must change."
OL,10,FDaniel Kebede, general secretary of
OL,11,Fthe National Education Union (NEU),
OL,12,Fsaid the response misses an
OL,13,Fopportunity "to take significant steps
OL,14,Ftowards meaningful change".
OL,16,F"The DfE's refusal to accept that
OL,17,Fsingle-word judgments should be
OL,18,Fscrapped will be met with dismay
OL,19,Facross the teaching profession," he
OL,20,Fsaid.
