OL,3,COfsted to keep single-phrase ratings
OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,F"It is especially welcome to hear from
OL,7,FDfE that it is open to ideas about how
OL,8,Fthe single-word judgments system could
OL,9,Fbe improved upon ` a set of policies
OL,10,Fthat the Government alone has the
OL,11,Fauthority to change.
OL,13,F"My committee agrees that there are
OL,14,Fbenefits to having a system of
OL,15,Fjudgments or ratings, such as the
OL,16,Fclarity they provide for parents.
OL,18,F"But we also maintain that a more
OL,19,Fnuanced version of this system is both
OL,20,Fachievable and in everyone's
OL,21,Finterests."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUzD@AOU}D@KO]
